      "Back to the purest of pure Sci-Fi Cheese.  This movie is also pure 80s, from the early scenes in the trailer park to the visual effects.  It’s pretty simple.. a guy in a trailer park is really good at some arcade game, which ends up being some kind of recruiting device to find starfighters to fight in some space war.  He gets recruited and eventually reluctantly accepts the job and so on.  There’s a book from a few years back called <strong>Armada</strong> that pretty much copied this formula, so this movie felt kind of familiar to me.  The movie has two actors from 80s movies that I really like: Catherine Mary Stewart from <strong>Night of the Comet (1984)</strong> and Lance Guest from <strong>Halloween II (1981)</strong>.  So that’s already a plus… and I enjoyed the first part of the movie.. it has that cozy 80s feel to it.  Once it gets to space, it gets a little worse.. the effects are very early CGI and pretty ugly.  The space part isn’t quite as epic as some of the other movies earlier in this week.  I still liked the charm of it all, I just wish it had a bit more of the epic adventure aspect to it in the later half.",
