      "Now here is a traditional giallo.  Mysterious killer, gruesome deaths, determined investigator and a big reveal at the end.  This is pretty much exactly what I think of when I think of a giallo, so that’s good.  The cozy 70s Italian setting is there too.  The story is basically of a missing/murdered little girl as well as various victims who get killed here and there.  The main character, the detective, is played by George Hilton who the blog remembers as the random Sartana that wasn’t played by Gianni Garko.  I think he is a good fit for this kind of determined detective role.  Pretty good, standard giallo, which is all I was hoping for this week.",
