      "Halfway through the slashers now and this one is a Lucio Fulci film.  The blu-ray case makes it looks like the title is “Murderock”.. but Letterboxd has other ideas.  Anyway, this is of course one of those giallo-like slashers but centered around a bunch of dancers.  So yeah, there is some cheesy dance stuff and music, but that’s mostly towards the beginning.  Then it evens out and becomes a standard giallo/slasher with the typical twist ending.  It’s not earth-shattering, but for an 80s slasher, having that bit of giallo artistry puts it at least a little above average.",
