      "This title sounds like it could be any horror movie but it’s a, you guessed it, slasher in the woods.  This one has a couple recognizable actors, like ol Joey Pants and Bob Cobb.. er, the Maestro.. from Seinfeld.  You’ve got an unstable bus driver that’s in charge of taking a group of people out to this wilderness.. there’s some internal conflict, people start dying and it’s a slasher.  This one has a bit more of that wilderness survival aspect to it rather than more of a fun camp vibe like many woods slashers.  So there isn’t a whole lot else to say about the movie, but it’s decently fun.  The group of characters is a little bit more interesting than some of the previous movies this week, at least.  I’d say it’s not bad as far as slashers go, though I prefer the more “fun” camp ones myself.",
