      "Hoo boy… Godzilla as a dad.  At one point, Godzilla was an intimidating presence, but now has become a caring father with some goofy music accompanying some goofy baby Godzilla moments.  If you take that aspect out of it, it’s a typical Godzilla movie.. people on an island, some other monster threats, etc.  The mantis and spider monsters are all right, but it’s hard to take Godzilla seriously in this one.  When standing next to baby Godzilla, he doesn’t look so huge.  The scale is kind of confusing in this movie, actually.. it’s really far from the origins of the Godzilla series, that’s for sure.  The movie has some entertainment value and is worth some laughs, but wow.. this was a weird direction to go in a giant monster movie series.",
