      "The first James Bond movie is about as “classic action” as it gets.  It’s probably a little wild that I haven’t seen the first James Bond movie but.. I’ll go a step further: I’ve never seen any James Bond movie.  Sure, I’ve seen clips, I’ve seen parodies and I played GoldenEye on the Nintendo 64… but, not being a big action guy, I never sat down to watch one.  That might be heresy but I’ve righted the wrong now.  After watching this one, I can understand why it became as popular as it did.  I really doubt there was anything quite like it in the early 60s and I can tell that it influenced action movies for decades after.  Watching it now, it’s still a fun adventure and, yeah, a bit dated culturally, but taking it for what it is, it’s fun.  I wasn’t expecting this movie to be so..tropical.  In my mind, I imagined James Bond always in urban areas, casinos, big formal gatherings, etc.  But it makes for a good adventure and they do end up in the bad guy’s evil base eventually.  I would watch more of the classic James Bond movies at some point, assuming they kind of build on this template.",
