      "At first, I was really confused by this prequel to <strong>Cool Runnings (1994)</strong>.  Yeah, kidding.  I bought this solely because it was Arrow and it looked promising.. 70s sci-fi with Bruce Dern.  It ends up being a kind of one-man show in a space base/station, which reminds me of <strong>Moon (2009)</strong> with Sam Rockwell.  However, Moon seemed to deal a lot more with philosophical topics and the question of identity.. Silent Running feels a bit more like a hippie nature movie but in space.  I don’t know if I really “got” the point other than this guy really wanted to preserve the forest on the space station and was going a little crazy.  The aesthetic is good.. about what I would expect from this era of sci-fi.. and the setup got me ready for something good.. but in the end, it didn’t quite live up to all that.  Partly because, like I said, I wasn’t sure what the point of it all was.  Second, although he does a decent job most of the time, sometimes the acting is a little awkward.. I don’t know if part of that is supposed to be how the character is or if they could have tried a few more takes to get something a little better.  It’s still an all right movie, but I had higher expectations for it.  If you like space sci-fi but with hippie nature folk music, this is it.",
