      "Starting the sci-fi group with a movie I was mostly familiar with due to the Simpsons Treehouse of Horror segment that parodied it.  I like the “last person alive” type of premise (ok, he isn’t the last person alive) since I think everyone wonders what they’d do if they had the whole world to themselves but were alone.  I guess I’d still collect movies, but may I’d move into an old video rental store.  After a while, a person would go crazy.  In a movie like this, I would have liked to see more of the “as it happened” aspect, instead of just dropping in when this guy has already been living this way for a while.  I think the physical and mental survival is the more interesting part of a post-apocalyptic setting.  I’ve seen <strong>The Last Man on Earth (1964)</strong> so I was aware of the premise from the original novel, but I wasn’t really aware that this movie was based on the same source.  For some reason, I thought there was a different angle to this one, so I guess I was a little disappointed that it wasn’t.  It’s an ok movie, but I found the first half a lot more interesting than the last.",
