      "Why randomly the 5th movie in the Harry Potter series, you might ask.  I bought an 8-film blu-ray set on eBay for cheaper than I saw it on Amazon thinking I got a good deal.  However, the discs all seem very.. different, no real consistency and there was a duplicate copy of the 4th film instead of the 5th.  So I’m thinking it’s a bootleg.. the dark spot of my movie collection.  Shame!  Shame!  Anyway, so I ended up seeing all but the Order of the Phoenix and bought it individually used later on.  So finally I’ve completed the Harry Potter journey.  I’m not really a Harry Potter guy.. I’m a <strong>Lord of the Rings </strong>trilogy man myself.  I didn’t grow up with either, so I don’t really have nostalgia either way.  I just prefer something a little less kid-oriented with a premise that feels a bit more universal.. I feel I can relate more to a hobbit on a journey to complete a quest than a kid who becomes a wizard.  Anyway, all that to say the Harry Potter movies are solid movies, but I lack that attachment that many people have who read the books or saw the movies when they were younger.  The middle films suffer the most for me.. not as fun and imaginative as the first ones and not as significant as the last ones.  I skipped from the 4th to 6th and, aside from a few key moments, I wouldn’t have even known there was a 5th movie between those two.  Still, I don’t dislike the movie.. the effects and settings are always great and it is a fun and creative world, but the plot and the characters don’t quite grab me",
