      "I’m gonna level with you.. I had never seen a Superman movie or TV show in my life.  But being THE superhero, I was pretty familiar with him, some backstory, his powers, etc.  So when I watched the movie, it wasn’t really “new” to me, except some of the details.  It’s a fun movie (fitting for the “Fun” Adventures category), but it does take a while to get going.  There is a lot of backstory and setup when I was just waiting to see the actual Superman stuff.  Once it gets to actual Superman mode, it’s fun.. but also very cartoonish (ok yeah I know, it’s a comic after all).  The villain and his bumbling sidekick, the cheesy Superman lines and the overly ridiculous powers all feel like those old 60s/70s cartoons in live action form.  It’s not really a criticism.. although, for me, I still prefer something just a <em>little</em> more realistic.  I can see why people would love it at the time, but it doesn’t age as well as some other movies from the era",
