      "Or <strong>Sartana the Gravedigger</strong> in some circles.  It was kind of confusing to figure out which movie is which among the Sartana series, especially with alternate titles.  This one was pretty fun.  The premise is that “Sartana” and a gang rob a bank for $300,000 and a $10,000 bounty is put on his head, causing several people to come after him, seeking the bounty.  Why I use quotes around “Sartana” is because it was not actually him, but someone pretending to be him.   The real Sartana doesn’t like that very much and goes on a hunt to find out who did it.  It’s a good premise since it gives you an excuse to go from place to place, gunfighting and what not.. but also a little bit of that investigation/mystery feel.  Because of the time it was made and the fact that it’s Italian, I got some giallo vibes from it.  All in all, a fun movie, but I still can’t get over the fact that Sartana is just <em>too</em> powerful, so there is never a lot of suspense about whether he’ll survive.  He wins every fight easily without a struggle.  The movie is a little cartoon-ish in that way and some of the things he does, but I guess that’s part of the fun.",
