      "All the Larry Fessenden movies up to this point have been leading to this.. I liked each one better than the one before so if that trend continues… eeeeyyy.  Unfortunately, maybe due to my heightened expectations, this one didn’t quite live up to the trend.  It was still good though.  I liked the cold, isolated station.. very similar to <strong>The Thing (1982)</strong>.  Like that movie, it has some internal conflicts here and there and there’s a psychological/paranoia element to it.  But this one has a much less defined “struggle”, if that’s the right term.  In The Thing, it’s clear what is happening and it gives meaning and impact to everything that happens.  In The Last Winter, it’s more of a mysterious “something” out in the snow.  Maybe it’s a personal preference, but I like the clearer idea of what’s happening.  The cast is pretty good, some recognizable faces, but there’s some pretty cheesy CGI that kind of ruins the mood.  I still like the setting and the overall feel of the movie, and this was definitely a little more activity than the previous Fessenden films, but it didn’t <em>quite</em> reach the heights I hoped for.  Still one of the better movies from this watchlist/tournament thing.",
