      "Sigh… I guess this is the last movie for the watchlist.. my initial goal was 45 (five per week for nine weeks) with a stretch of 63 (two bonus movies per week) and finally, I saw 70 was in reach so I decided that’d be a nice even number.  So here we are at #70, a strange one to end on.  As the name would suggest, it is a comedy.  The style of comedy is a <em>little</em> bit like a Mel Brooks movie but tamer.  There’s a bit of slapstick, too.  Normally, I would probably dislike something like this (from my experience with another comedy attempt like <strong>The Invisible Woman</strong>), but this has a list of horror stars who are good comedic actors too.  While the jokes were not always so great, the facial expressions and reactions of these guys were usually at least entertaining.  Overall, there’s some fun here but it won’t change anyone’s life.. probably",
