      "I’m a fan of horror anthology movies, but I tend to prefer those who feature four or five stories.  Fewer than that, they just linger too long and more than that are too short to get into anything before it’s over.  Twice Told Tales falls in the “fewer” category with three stories, which is not so bad in itself, but the movie is two hours, so that’s roughly 40 minutes per segment on average.  I liked the first segment the best with two older men finding a kind of youth elixir.  The second segment was a “forbidden love” type situation which had an interesting premise but dragged too much.  The final one is the House of the Seven Gables.  Great setting and everything, but again, just a bit too slow.  In the realm of horror anthology, this is a little above average, but I think with shorter segments and maybe just one additional segment, it would have been much higher on my scale.",
