      "Man, I actually had some fun with this one.  Again, it’s really not even remotely horror, despite being on this “Universal Horror Collection” from Scream Factory.  Putting that aside, it accomplishes what some of these other movies couldn’t, which is just being entertaining.  Maybe it’s because it stars Boris Karloff and he has a fun, loyal sidekick, Petty Louie.  Otherwise, it’s similar to the other ones (unnecessary romance sub-plot, criminals as the main villains, no deaths/monsters/scares), but it just does everything a little bit better.  This is one I’d watch again or at least throw on in the background when I’m doing something else.",
