      "Week 5 is Universal horror, but these aren’t the classic monsters.  Instead, these come from a series of blu ray sets that Scream Factory has put out of various Universal horror movies.  On to the leadoff hitter, <strong>Murders in the Zoo</strong>.  Short and simple, but for its age, pretty entertaining.  This one had nothing supernatural, just a crazy, jealous guy who would murder men just for hitting on his wife.  They have some live animals that I guess were semi-tranquilized but I still wouldn’t trust being around some of those animals.. but that’s just me and I wasn’t born for another half century, so what does my opinion matter.  Anyway, these old films are pretty cozy, so I’m looking forward to the rest of the week.",
