      "Just squeezed in a bonus movie this week but it’s a bit different.  This time, it’s the documentary packaged with the blu ray set.  I felt like it’d be good to know more about this guy after watching a few of his movies and, as the title mentions, his death is a story in itself.  Anyway, it’s always funny to see these stories about exploitation filmmakers who do anything to capitalize on the success of something else and it seems like he did a pretty good job of it.  Although none of the movies I watched this week are what I’d consider “good”, he made his movies with the budget and constraints that he had and was able to make them mostly entertaining and somewhat coherent, despite all of the editing and shuffling after filming.  I’m sure I’ll return to the Al Adamson vault sometime, maybe on a lazy Saturday afternoon when a cheap 70s genre movie sounds appealing",
