      "Well this wasn’t exactly what I was thinking about when I grouped together some unwatched 90s horror movies.  This is more of an old school Italian giallo movie that just happened to be made in the 90s, not the grunge/alternative music and/or boy band music video style I had in mind for this week’s theme.  Even so, it was still an entertaining and disturbing movie, although it’s kind of a rip-off of another wax-related movie.. so maybe not the most original premise.  It’s a period piece rather than modern day and there aren’t too many “historical” horror movies compared to more modern settings, so it’s at least got that going for it.",
